headline: Sales Development Representative @Theneo
about:
I thrive at the intersection of technology, communication, and problem-solving. As an SDR at Theneo, I currently help connect companies with solutions that make developer experiences smoother. Along the way, I’ve also built experience in content strategy, client onboarding, and project management.

I love tackling new challenges, learning on the fly, and finding creative ways to make processes more efficient. Outside of main work, I also enjoy exploring writing and copywriting projects - they keep my creativity active and help me communicate ideas clearly and effectively.

I’m always happy to connect with professionals to share insights, exchange ideas, or explore opportunities to work together.

experience.description:
- Review, modify, and adjust content for over 30 companies, ensuring alignment with client-specific needs and expectations.

- Gain in-depth knowledge of each company’s content and processes, allowing for tailored content adjustments and effective coordination.

- Coordinated and managed executive calendars, scheduling meetings, appointments, and events to optimize time and resource utilization.
- Prepared, organized, and maintained important documents and reports, implementing efficient filing systems to streamline document retrieval.
- Handled incoming and outgoing communications, including emails and phone calls, providing timely and professional responses to inquiries.
- Supported meetings by preparing agendas, taking minutes, and following up on action items to ensure timely completion and effective communication.

- Acted as the initial point of contact for all incoming inquiries, introducing the service to potential clients and managing 50-60 requests daily.
- Answered questions, provided detailed service information, and guided clients through the onboarding process, contributing to a smooth and efficient client journey.
- Handled both email and phone communications, ensuring clear and prompt responses to client needs.
- Integrated into the client outreach process via various social media channels, actively engaging with clients to better understand and address their needs.

- Supported up to 100 students daily, assisting with their understanding of the educational process and enhancing their learning experience.
- Attended seminars and lectures alongside the professor, providing additional academic support and guidance to students.
- Reviewed and graded written materials and facilitated discussions, ensuring a comprehensive understanding of course content among students.

headline: Manual QA Engineer at Theneo (YC W22)

experience.description:
1. Design and execute comprehensive manual test plans and test cases based on product requirements and user stories.
2. Identify, document, and track defects using tools like Jira.
3. Perform functional, integration, regression, and exploratory testing to validate product stability and performance.
4. Collaborate closely with developers and product managers to ensure features meet quality standards before release.
5. Provide clear, concise, and actionable bug reports and work closely with the engineering team to resolve issues.
6. Participate in sprint planning, reviews, and daily standups to ensure timely testing and feedback loops.
7. Validate bug fixes and ensure that issues are resolved without causing regression in other areas of the product.
8. Contribute to the development and continuous improvement of QA processes, test plans, and strategies.
9. Ensure cross-browser and cross-platform compatibility for the platform.

1. Working closely with PO, PM, developers, UI/UX designers, and testers
2. Participating in all scrum meetings
3. Reviewing and analyzing business requirements
4. Create positive and negative test cases based on business requirements
5. Test website functionality in positive and negative ways
6. Test website front-end and UI in different browsers
7. Test website back-end logic using Swagger and Postman
6. Creating detailed bug reports in Jira
7. Conduct re-testing when bugs are fixed
8. Conduct regression testing on the staging environments before release
9. Conduct regression testing on production

projects.description: The Eat n Split project is a web application designed to simplify group dining experiences by allowing users to split bills and track individual expenses. The project leverages React to build a dynamic and responsive interface that enhances user interaction and functionality.

projects.description: The Far Away project is a travel planning web application that allows users to create and manage a personalized list of items they need for their trips. Designed to help users organize their travel essentials efficiently, the application features a user-friendly interface and interactive elements.

projects.title: Forkify
projects.description: Developed the Forkify project, a dynamic web application that allows users to search for recipes, add their own recipes, and bookmark favorites for easy access. Utilized Vanilla JavaScript, HTML, and CSS to build a responsive and interactive user interface. Through this project, I gained a solid understanding of the MVC (Model-View-Controller) design pattern, which improved code maintainability and scalability by 40%.

projects.title: NoteApp

This project enhanced my fullstack development skills and provided hands-on experience in building a complete, user-friendly application from scratch.
